This means more than 76 million Americans have a monthly mortgage payment due each month.
3] Home Buyers Are Waiting to Buy or Lowering OffersHome buyers are also having to adjust course during this time.
A whopping 55 % of would-be buyers are putting off their purchase for now or no longer have plans to buy.
4] Renters Are Struggling to PayRenters are in a similar situation as homeowners and wondering how they will pay their bills.
Nearly half of renters surveyed said they had less than $500 in a savings account prior to the pandemic.